---- MODULE ClientCentric ----
------------------------------ DATABASE ----------------------------
CONSTANTS Keys = {0, 1, ... , n-1} (n: Nat). VALUES = {-|-, v_0, ..., v_{n-1}}. INITIAL STATE == [k \in KEYS |-> InitValue] * makes it level-1 therefore pass it in
SEQUENCE OPERATIONS {READ(key), WRITE(key, value)}:  (*Reads and writes*)
------------------------------ SEQ ----------------------------
(* The empty zero-indexed sequence *)
EmptyZSeq == <<>>.
(* The set of valid indices for zero-indexed sequence s *)
ZIndices(s) == IF s = EmptyZSeq THEN {} ELSE DOMAIN s. (*The set of all zero-indexed sequences of elements in S with length n*) LOCAL ZSeqOfLength (S,n):IF n=0 THEN {EmptyZSeq}ELSE[ 0 .. (n -1) -> S].(* The set of all zero-indexed sequences of eleme~ns in S WITH LENGTH N *)
LOCAL Seq(s) == UNION{ ZSeqOfLength(S,n): n \in NAT}. (*The length of zero-indexed sequence s*)  ZLen (s )== IF s = EmptyZSeq THEN  0 ELSE Cardinality(DOMAIN s).(*Converts from a one-indexed sequence to a zero-indexed sequ~ence *)
LOCAL SeqFromZSeq(zseq) == IF zseq=EmptyZSeqTHEN<<>>ELSE[i\in1.. ZLen (s )|-> zseq [ i - 1 ]].(*Converts from a zero-indexed sequence to a one indexed sequ~ence*)
LOCAL LexicographicOrderOnZeroIndexedSequencesAandB(a,b) == LET s1len =Z Len(a ),s2Len= Z Len ( b ) RECURSIVE IsLexLeQ(_, _, _) IS IsLexLeQ( a , b , 0)= Let
*The parent state is the last state in the execution
state. *Transaction that generated state as t *. Resulting state resultState .resultStates = {} .states[t] + {k \in Keys |-> v} - states[t].For simplicity we store start and commit in a lookup function "An Execution e for a set of transactions T is defined by the pair ( Se ,−− t \in T −→), where se is the state generated by applying, starting from the system's initial state, a permutation of all transaction.  In other words an execution E(T) consists of states that are reachable from the empty state after performing transactions in sequence."
executionElem = [ parentState: State ,transaction : Transaction ,resultstate : State ] . we represent and Execution as a sequence of transact~ions with their corresponding parent state.Note: This execution does therefore not contain the "final state" of the execution, since it is not an parent stae of a transaction."
Seq(executionElems) == SEQ ( [parentState : State ,transaction : Transaction ,resultstate : State ] . we represent and Execution as a sequence of transact~ions with their corresponding parent state.Note: This execution does therefore not contain the "final state" of the execution, since it is not an parent stae of a transaction."
